## Examples and Types of Hostile Conduct

Hostile work environments often involve discriminatory harassment, which can manifest in various forms:

| Type of Conduct          | Description                                                  | Examples                                                  |
|-------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------|
| **Verbal Harassment**    | Offensive comments or jokes related to protected traits      | Racial slurs, sexist jokes, derogatory remarks about religion or disability |
| **Physical Harassment**  | Unwelcome touching or physical intimidation                   | Unwanted sexual advances, physical threats                |
| **Visual Harassment**    | Displaying offensive materials                                | Sexually suggestive photos, racist images                  |
| **Behavioral Harassment**| Actions that isolate, demean, or belittle based on protected class | Excluding someone from meetings due to their gender or race |

Sexual harassment is a common form of hostile work environment, but it is not the only form. Racial harassment, age discrimination, and disability-based harassment are equally recognized ([Wikipedia, n.d.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hostile_work_environment); [Workable, n.d.](https://resources.workable.com/stories-and-insights/hostile-work-environment-signs-fixes)).

